The moment you deicide to sign a TX or perform a GPG operation you observe a specific state.

Your private key is chilling in superposition... Is it GPG? Is it Bitcoin? Boom. Both.

Your private key doesn't exist in a superposition of dead and alive cat.

Your private key is now a qubit.
No one knows that these addresses and fingerprints come from the same private key... b/c that is kinda how asymmetric cryptography works.
You distribute the resulting addresses and fingerprints far and wide.
You derive a GPG key, an SSH key, a Bitcoin address and a Namecoin address all from the same private key.
